# Citation File Format v1.2.0 — https://citation-file-format.github.io/
#
# Powers GitHub's "Cite this repository" UI button on the noheton/shepard
# repo. Cite this fork when reporting work that depends on the additive
# /v2 surface, plugin SPI, MCP server, AI plugin, or any of the
# fork-specific features. For the upstream shepard project, see
# the `references` section below or cite the upstream repository
# directly at gitlab.com/dlr-shepard/shepard.

cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "shepard — Storage for HEterogeneous Product And Research Data (noheton fork)"
message: >-
  If you use this fork's additive /v2 surface, plugin SPI, MCP server,
  AI plugin, or Helmholtz Unhide publish path, please cite it as below.
  For citations of the upstream shepard codebase, prefer the upstream
  CITATION.cff at gitlab.com/dlr-shepard/shepard.
type: software
abstract: >-
  A multi-database research-data platform from DLR's Center for Lightweight
  Production Technology in Augsburg. Exposes a single REST API over Neo4j
  (metadata graph), MongoDB (structured / files), Postgres+TimescaleDB
  (timeseries), and S3-compatible object storage (Garage by default).
  This fork adds an additive /v2 surface, a plugin SPI (PayloadKind /
  PayloadStorage / LlmProvider / Minter / Sidecar), an MCP server for Claude
  and other MCP clients, an AI plugin with PROV-O capture, Helmholtz Unhide
  publish, view recipes, and a v1 deprecation control plane. Preserves
  byte-for-byte compatibility with upstream shepard 5.2.0 on /shepard/api/*.

